  "response_text": "Here's a 3-day meal plan that incorporates heart-healthy foods to support a healthy cardiovascular system:\n\n**Day 1**\n\n* **Breakfast**: Oatmeal with banana, almond butter, and a splash of low-fat milk\n\t+ 1 cup cooked oatmeal\n\t+ 1 medium banana, sliced\n\t+ 2 tbsp almond butter\n\t+ 1/2 cup low-fat milk\n* **Lunch**: Grilled chicken breast with roasted vegetables and quinoa\n\t+ 4 oz grilled chicken breast\n\t+ 1 cup mixed roasted vegetables (such as broccoli, carrots, and bell peppers)\n\t+ 1/2 cup cooked quinoa\n* **Dinner**: Baked salmon with sweet potato and green beans\n\t+ 6 oz baked salmon\n\t+ 1 medium sweet potato, baked\n\t+ 1 cup steamed green beans\n* **Snack**: Apple slices with peanut butter\n\t+ 1 medium apple, sliced\n\t+ 2 tbsp peanut butter\n\n**Day 2**\n\n* **Breakfast**: Greek yogurt with berries and granola\n\t+ 6 oz Greek yogurt\n\t+ 1/2 cup mixed berries (such as blueberries, strawberries, and raspberries)\n\t+ 2 tbsp granola\n* **Lunch**: Turkey and avocado wrap with mixed greens\n\t+ 1 whole wheat tortilla\n\t+ 2 oz sliced turkey breast\n\t+ 1/2 avocado, sliced\n\t+ 1 cup mixed greens\n* **Dinner**: Grilled turkey burger with roasted Brussels sprouts and brown rice\n\t+ 4 oz grilled turkey burger\n\t+ 1 cup roasted Brussels sprouts\n\t+ 1/2 cup cooked brown rice\n* **Snack**: Carrot sticks with hummus\n\t+ 4-6 carrot sticks\n\t+ 2 tbsp hummus\n\n**Day 3**\n\n* **Breakfast**: Smoothie bowl with spinach, banana, and almond milk\n\t+ 2 cups spinach\n\t+ 1 medium banana\n\t+ 1 cup almond milk\n\t+ 1/2 cup sliced almonds\n* **Lunch**: Grilled chicken breast with mixed greens and a balsamic vinaigrette dressing\n\t+ 4 oz grilled chicken breast\n\t+ 2 cups mixed greens\n\t+ 2 tbsp balsamic vinaigrette dressing\n* **Dinner**: Shrimp and vegetable stir-fry with brown rice\n\t+ 4 oz cooked shrimp\n\t+ 1 cup mixed stir-fried vegetables (such as bell peppers, onions, and snow peas)\n\t+ 1/2 cup cooked brown rice\n* **Snack**: Cottage cheese with cucumber slices\n\t+ 1/2 cup cottage cheese\n\t+ 4-6 cucumber slices\n\nThis meal plan incorporates heart-healthy foods such as:\n\n* Fatty fish (salmon and shrimp) rich in omega-3 fatty acids\n* Lean protein sources (chicken breast, turkey breast, and turkey burger)\n* Whole grains (quinoa, brown rice, and whole wheat tortilla)\n* Fresh fruits and vegetables (berries, apples, carrots, broccoli, and sweet potatoes)\n* Healthy fats (almond butter, peanut butter, and avocado)\n* Low-fat dairy products (Greek yogurt and cottage cheese)\n\nRemember to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day. Also, consult with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian to create a personalized meal plan that suits your specific needs and health goals.",
